# Selection Framework

## Purpose

Selection is an architectural concept, not a trading concept.

It provides a reusable framework for choosing one object from a set of eligible candidates.

---

# Mathematical Model

R = P(G(O))

where

O = Observations

G = Candidate Generator

P = Selection Policy

R = Selected Result

---

# Definitions

## Candidate

A Candidate is an object satisfying the eligibility predicate for a particular selection problem.

---

## Candidate Generator

A deterministic function producing the complete and sound candidate set.

Properties:

- Complete
- Sound
- Deterministic

---

## Selection Policy

A deterministic policy selecting one candidate from a candidate set.

---

# Selection Axiom

Every deterministic selection problem is decomposed into

Observations

↓

Candidate Generator

↓

Candidate Set

↓

Selection Policy

↓

Selected Result

---

# Selection Uniqueness Theorem

If

- Candidate Set ≠ ∅

and

- Selection Policy induces a total order

then exactly one candidate is selected.

---

# Architectural Properties

- Deterministic
- Sound
- Complete
- Explainable
- Total